          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1634641446809-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pork steak<strong> </strong>is browned on one side, reduce the heat to medium-high, flip and cook 1 min further</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> chicken stock</strong> and <strong>sliced leeks</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 4 min or until the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1634641449984-x200.jpg",
